 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $V\subseteq K^{m}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $W\subseteq K^{n}$
\end_inset

 be varieties.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi:V\to W$
\end_inset

 is said to be a 
\series bold
polynomial mapping 
\series default
(or 
\series bold
regular mapping
\series default
) if there exist polynomials 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{1},\dots,f_{n}\in K[x_{1},\dots,x_{m}]$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi(a_{1},\dots,a_{m})=(f_{1}(a_{1},\dots,a_{m}),\dots,f_{n}(a_{1},\dots,a_{m}))
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $(a_{1},\dots,a_{m})\in V$
\end_inset

.
 We say that the 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-tuple of polynomials 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
(f_{1},\dots,f_{n})\in(K[x_{1},\dots,x_{m}])^{n}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
represents 
\series default

\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{i}$
\end_inset

 are the 
\series bold
components 
\series default
of this representation.
 
